**StudentProfile Class Definition**  
The `StudentProfile` class is designed to encapsulate the essential details of a university undergraduate student. It includes the student's legal name, a unique identifier, and their GPA. The class provides methods to access and modify these attributes, ensuring data integrity and encapsulation.

```cpp
class StudentProfile {
private:
    std::string name;
    int studentID;
    double gpa;

public:
    StudentProfile(const std::string& name, int studentID, double gpa);
    ~StudentProfile();

    std::string getName() const;
    int getStudentID() const;
    double getGPA() const;

    void setName(const std::string& name);
    void setStudentID(int studentID);
    void setGPA(double gpa);

    void displayProfile() const;
};
```

